<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870423-0076 </DOCNO><HL> B.F. Goodrich StakeIs Increased to 7.6%</HL><DD> 04/23/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GRTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   A group led by New York investor George Soros raised its stake in B.F. Goodrich Co. to 7.6% of the common shares outstanding.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, the Soros group said it holds 1,731,400 Goodrich common shares. The group's most recent transactions in Goodrich common stock include purchases of 343,700 shares from March 12 through April 16 at $51.254 to $57.32 a share and sales of 1,900 shares April 16 at $52.75 each, the filing said.    According to the filing, group members acquired their Goodrich stock for investment purposes. Akron, Ohio-based Goodrich is a plastics and specialty chemicals company that is also 50% owner of a major tire producer.    Goodrich officials couldn't be reached for comment.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading, Goodrich closed at $52.75, down 50 cents. </TEXT></DOC>